statenotes:
2 deaths cross notified to other states from Chennai and Coimbatore.
1 patient died after turning negative for infection in Chengalpattu

[10-May]
Delhi bulletins in the morning, containing data of the previous day. We will add that data to the date on which the report is released, rather than the previous day.

- Cases updated as per WB bulletin.
- Deaths due to comorbidities added to total deceased
MoHFW website reports that these are the "cases that are being reassigned to states"

Total includes patients from other states and a new category "Foreign Evacuees" which is now reported in AP bulletin.
AP district data updated to match state dashboard as of 27th May.
Two active cases in KA reduced as these confirmed patients died of non-CoViD19 related reasons

Includes one case from Nagaland
Total of three* patients who migrated to other states has been reduced from Active count
Mahe native who expired in Kannur included in Kerala's tally
Three migrated cases reduced from Active count
HP has 4 Migrated cases which are reduced from Active #. Also, death of Tibetan refugee is included in deceased numbers, but not in confirmed
Two cases have migrated out of Tripura.

state: Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Daman and Diu
